title: Court temporarily bars federal officials from removing Texas border wire
description: A Texas court issued a temporary restraining order barring federal officials from removing concertina wire placed along the border as part of Operation Lone Star.

title: An angry mob at an Israeli university stirs fears of Jewish-Arab violence
description: Israel has largely avoided the kind of communal strife that shook the country during the conflict between Israel and Hamas in 2021. But the tide could be turning.

title: Why are Israel and Hamas at war? A basic explainer.
description: On Oct. 7, 2023, Hamas militants launched an unprecedented attack on Israel. Here is a basic explainer of the reasons behind the latest war.

title: What is Hezbollah, the militant group on Israel’s northern border?
description: Hezbollah and Israel, longtime enemies, have traded shelling since Hamas’s attack on Israel.

title: As settler violence surges, West Bank Palestinians fear new displacement
description: At least seven Palestinians have been killed by Israeli settlers since the war in Gaza began, rights groups say, and hundreds have been driven from their homes.

title: Hurricane Otis death toll rises to 45; dozens still missing
description: Rescue workers searched the Acapulco rubble with cadaver dogs while authorities assessed the damage wrought by the sudden Category 5 storm.

title: The Gaza Strip and its history, explained
description: In its war with Hamas, Israel has ordered a siege on the Gaza Strip, one of the world’s most densely populated and impoverished territories.

title: Israel tanks penetrate deep into Gaza, as Hamas hostage video emerges
description: Israeli forces reported moving deeper into the Gaza Strip and directly engaging Hamas militants as the ground incursions gather pace.

title: ‘The Empty Grave of Comrade Bishop’: Podcast episode guide
description: An episode guide: Grenada’s Prime Minister was executed in a coup in 1983. The location of his remains is unknown. New details reveal the role the U.S. played.

title: China and Russia cast U.S. as agent of global instability at military forum
description: While both China and Russia warned that the United States was making the world more dangerous, Beijing left the way open for improved military cooperation.

title: Journalists killed in the Israel-Gaza war: A look at the lives lost
description: At least 29 journalists have been killed in the Israel-Gaza war since Oct. 7; the majority of those killed so far, 24, were Palestinians in the Gaza Strip.

title: Israel-Gaza war live updates: U.S. negotiated to restore internet, send more aid to Gaza, officials say
description: Washington pressured Israel to restore communications in the Gaza Strip as it expanded its ground and air assault, senior U.S. officials told The Post.

title: New Zealanders are blasting Celine Dion until 3 a.m., leaving some miserable
description: The young people in New Zealand’s “siren clubs” say they’re expressing themselves by blasting the loudest, cleanest sound from their speakers.

title: Extremist attacks escalate in Niger after coup topples American ally
description: Western officials say there are now “few barriers to growth” for Islamist militant terrorist groups.

title: Protesters storm Russian airport to try to block plane from Tel Aviv
description: More than 20 people were injured in the incident, which occurred after Telegram channels based in Dagestan called for people to “catch” Israelis on the flight.

title: As Israel bombards Gaza, a woman sees her world collapse
description: Thousands of families across the Gaza Strip have lost relatives and friends in Israeli bombardments since Hamas’s attack on Israel on Oct. 7.

title: Threats against Cornell’s Jewish students reported to FBI, school says
description: Cornell University police notified the FBI of a potential hate crime after antisemitic messages threatened violence to Cornell’s Jewish community.
